.Dd April 2, 2026
.Dt ZPOOL-REBALANCE 8
.Os
.
.Sh NAME
.Nm zpool-rebalance
.Nd rebalance an AnyRAID vdev in a ZFS storage pool
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm zpool
.Cm rebalance
.Ar pool Ar anyraid-vdev
.
.Sh DESCRIPTION
Starts a rebalance operation on an AnyRAID vdev.
If a relocate operation is already in progress, this command will fail.
This operation will proceed in the background, moving tiles from more fill
leaf vdevs to less full ones in order to optimize potential space usage and
balance read workload across devices.
When the relocate finishes, the pool will be scrubbed to verify the integrity
of all the moved data.
.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr zpoolconcepts 7 ,
.Xr zpool-status 8
